data.content:
Three breaking changes hit your code. Here's each one:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` — now takes `Func<>`, not `Expression<Func<>>`

Your expression-tree construction **won't compile** anymore. The fix is dramatically simpler — just use a regular lambda with conditionals:

```csharp
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

Delete all the `Expression.Lambda` / `Expression.Call` / `Expression.Parameter` code.

---

### 2. Complex type columns — two changes

**a) Duplicate names are now uniquified.** `ShippingAddress.Street` and `BillingAddress.Street` previously silently shared one column — now EF appends a number (e.g., `Street`, `Street1`). To keep the old mapping, pin column names explicitly:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress,
        p => p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress,
        p => p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
});
```

**b) Nested complex types now use the full path.** `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` was mapped to column `BillingAddress_City` — now it becomes `Payment_BillingAddress_City`. To preserve the old name:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>()
    .ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment)
    .ComplexProperty(p => p.BillingAddress)
    .Property(a => a.City)
    .HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");
```

⚠️ Both changes affect **existing migrations** — after upgrading, `dotnet ef migrations add` will generate column renames. Pin names if you want to avoid a migration diff.

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` — new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method gained a `string logCommandText` parameter (for redacted SQL logging). Add it to your implementation:

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection,
        DbCommand command,
        DbContext context,
        Guid commandId,
        Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)   // ← new parameter
    {
        // Use logCommandText for logging (constants may be redacted)
        // Use command.CommandText for actual executed SQL
    }
}
```

Update **all** methods on the interface (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.) the same way.
